 -- Jean-Luc Lamadon <jean-luc.lamadon@nokia.com>  Thu, 25 Mar 2010 17:06:49 +0200

libcontentaction (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * All actions are defined in .desktop files.
  * Tracker-based conditions and highlighter regexps are defined in the
    configuration files.
  * New API to create Action:s for URI schemes (like mailto:).
  * Defaultness related methods of Action are gone, there is a new API for
    setting defaults.
  * Added functions to selectively highlight and remove all highlighting
    from DuiLabels.
  * lca-tool synopsis changed.
  * New binary package: libcontentaction-data, containing configuration files.
  * Package libcontentaction-dui removed, now libcontentaction depends on
    libdui unconditionally.

 -- Akos PASZTORY <ext-akos.pasztory@nokia.com>  Mon, 22 Mar 2010 10:01:25 +0200

